description:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Location&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cygnet Derby, 100 London Road, Derby, DE24 8WZ&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;£8.72 to £10.08 per hour + Enhancements for nights/weekends/bank holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full Time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role you’ll have the chance to make a real impact on patients, service users &amp; their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cygnet Hospital Derby provides low secure and mental health rehabilitation care based on the Recovery Model.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently recruiting for Care and Support workers forLitchurch Ward,which is our male low secure service and can support up to 15 men who have mental health or dual/multiple diagnosis needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an active member of our dynamic team, you’ll provide support for our nursing staff including the admission, assessment, implementation and discharge of inpatients, with a focus on dignity and safety at all times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role you’ll:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with a DBT Based Model on a Ward with Dedicated Psychology Input&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Offer enhanced care with a flexible learning approach for all our patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Females with Emotionally Unstable Personality Disorders to build better lives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in a Low Secure Environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist patients with their medical and welfare needs and report as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safeguard patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn about individuals’ specific needs and provide help in the most appropriate way.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;re looking for people who have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills and the ability to be a good team player&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The sensitivity and energy required to provide a trusting, stimulating and varied lifestyle for the patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A genuine desire to make a real difference in people’s lives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong, flexible mental aptitude and an ability to cope with the physical demands of the role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NVQ level 1 or 2 in a relevant care setting is preferable but not essential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In return, you’ll receive a competitive salary and a range of benefits including:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fantastic Learning/Training Opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee Discount Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;DBS paid&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regular coaching and support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributory pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health Cash Plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Subsidised meals on duty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good Transport Links &amp; Close to centre of Derby&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free Parking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note: successful candidates will be required to undergo an enhanced DBS check.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Location Information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Litchurch Ward&lt;/strong&gt;is our male low secure service and can support up to 15 men who have mental health or dual/multiple diagnosis needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ward is suitable for people who are moving on from medium security placements and who have engaged in dangerous and/or chronic challenging behaviour and who may pose a continuing and ongoing risk to others or themselves. We can also support people who represent a persistent risk of absconding to avoid treatment, those who find it difficult to engage and those who have a dual or multiple diagnosis, which could include substance misuse and/or personality disorder.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
